wd:Q55786360 a med:Disease ;
    rdfs:label "8p11.2 deletion syndrome"@en ;
    schema1:description "8p11.2 deletion syndrome is a contiguous gene syndrome characterized by the association of congenital spherocytosis, dysmorphic features, growth delay and hypogonadotropic hypogonadism."@en .

wd:Q55786361 a med:Disease ;
    rdfs:label "8p23.1 microdeletion syndrome"@en ;
    schema1:description "8p23.1 deletion involves a partial deletion of the short arm of chromosome 8 characterized by low birth weight, postnatal growth deficiency, mild intellectual deficit, hyperactivity, craniofacial abnormalities, and congenital heart defects."@en .

